ver_button      = Yes\n| silver_year        = 2016\n| gold_button        = \n| gold_year          = \n| diamond_button     = \n| diamond_year       = \n| ruby_button        = \n| ruby_year          = \n| stats_update= April 2019\n}}\n\n}}\n<!-- {{Infobox YouTube personality|silver_button=yes|silver_year=2016|gold_button=no|gold_year=}} -->\n\n'''Lauren Cherie Southern''' (born 16 June<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=875795715116589056 |user=Lauren_Southern |title=It's my birthday so the only thing I want to see in my notifications today are pictures of your pets or anime versions of politicians. TY. |last=Southern |first=Lauren |author-link=Lauren Southern |date=16 June 2017 |access-date=27 July 2017 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170727172413/https://twitter.com/lauren_southern/status/875795715116589056 |archive-date=27 July 2017 |url-status=live |link=yes}}</ref> 1995) is a former  Canadian [[Right-libertarianism|right-wing libertarian]]  [[political activist]], Journalist  and [[YouTuber]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCla6APLHX6W3FeNLc8PYuvg|title=Lauren Southern|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2020-04-25}}</ref>. In 2015, Southern ran as a [[Libertarian Party of Canada|Libertarian Party]] candidate in the [[2015 Canadian federal election|Canadian federal election]]. She worked for [[The Rebel Media]] until March 2017, doing independent work before subsequently retiring from political activism in June 2019. \n\nSouthern is known for her promotion of [[the Great Replacement conspiracy theory]]. A [[YouTube]] video of the same name she released in July 2017<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/12/04/the-french-origins-of-you-will-not-replace-us|title=The French Origins of \"You Will Not Replace Us\"|last=Williams|first=Thomas Chatterton|date=4 December 2017|work=[[The New Yorker]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190814185144/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/12/04/the-french-origins-of-you-will-not-replace-us|archive-date=14 August 2019|access-date=7 August 2019}}</ref> has more than 680,000 views<ref>{{Cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OTDmsmN43NA|title=The Great Replacement|date=3 July 2017|last=Southern|first=Lauren|access-date=4 August 2019|via=YouTube}}</ref> and is credited with helping to popularize the white supremacist conspiracy theory.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/the-great-replacement-the-racist-idea-now-at-the-heart-of-europe-s-politics-20190319-p515cc.html|title='The Great Replacement': an idea now at the heart of Europe's politics|last1=Miller|first1=Nick|date=19 March 2019|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|accessdate=4 April 2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200124033850/https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/the-great-replacement-the-racist-idea-now-at-the-heart-of-europe-s-politics-20190319-p515cc.html|archive-date=24 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Southern supported the white [[Identitarian movement|Identitarian]] group [[Defend Europe]] opposing the action of [[non-governmental organization]]s (NGOs) involved in [[search-and-rescue]] operations in the [[Mediterranean Sea]].<ref name=\"Claxton2017\" /> She was [[Detention (imprisonment)|detained]] by the [[Italian Coast Guard]] for blocking a ship embarking on a search-and-rescue mission.<ref name=\"Claxton2017\">{{cite news|url=https://www.abbynews.com/news/former-langley-libertarian-candidate-detained-in-italy|title=Former Langley Libertarian candidate detained in Italy|last=Claxton|first=Matthew|date=17 May 2017|work=[[Abbotsford News]]|accessdate=13 March 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180314044039/https://www.abbynews.com/news/former-langley-libertarian-candidate-detained-in-italy|archivedate=14 March 2018}}</ref> In March 2018, she was questioned under the UK Terrorism Act<ref name=\"BBC_Entry\"/> and barred from entering Britain because of her intentions during her March visit.<ref name=\"NationalPost\">{{cite news|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/far-right-figures-say-they-were-deported-from-britain|title=Canadian far-right activist Lauren Southern barred from Britain for anti-Muslim views|date=12 March 2018|newspaper=[[National Post]]|accessdate=2 August 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180313161751/http://nationalpost.com/news/canada/far-right-figures-say-they-were-deported-from-britain|archive-date=13 March 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indBan\" />\n\nIn July 2018, she went on a speaking tour of Australia with [[Stefan Molyneux]]. In August 2018, her attempted speaking tour of New Zealand was unsuccessful and censored. The [[Auckland Council]] cancelled Southern's booking of a council venue and blocked her from using its venues, saying she wished to \"stir up ethnic or religious tensions\".<ref name=\"radionz\">{{cite news|url=https://www.radionz.co.nz/news/national/361220/far-right-pair-banned-from-speaking-at-auckland-council-venues-phil-goff|title=Far-right pair banned from speaking at Auckland Council venues \u2013 Phil Goff|last=Hatton|first1=Emma|date=6 July 2018|work=|accessdate=9 July 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710143343/https://www.rnz.co.nz/news/national/361220/far-right-pair-banned-from-speaking-at-auckland-council-venues-phil-goff|archive-date=10 July 2019|publisher=[[Radio New Zealand]]}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 June 2019, she announced on her website that she was stepping back from public life to resume her education.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://laurensouthern.net/a-new-chapter/|title=A New Chapter|last1=Southern|first1=Lauren|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190603023431/https://laurensouthern.net/a-new-chapter/|archivedate=3 June 2019|accessdate=3 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Education and personal life==\nSouthern was born in [[Surrey, British Columbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.libertarian.ca/candidate/lauren-southern|title=Lauren Southern profile|publisher=[[Libertarian Party of Canada]]|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610191650/https://www.libertarian.ca/candidate/lauren-southern|archivedate=10 June 2016|accessdate=1 July 2016}}</ref> She studied [[political science]] at the [[University of the Fraser Valley]] and completed two years without graduating.<ref name=\"V\">{{cite news|last=Khandaker|first=Tamara|url=https://news.vice.com/en_ca/article/8xmyaa/lauren-southern-is-the-alt-rights-not-so-secret-weapon|title=Lauren Southern is the alt-right\u2019s not-so-secret weapon|date=10 March 2017|access-date=19 July 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200124025630/https://www.vice.com/en_ca/article/8xmyaa/lauren-southern-is-the-alt-rights-not-so-secret-weapon|archive-date=24 January 2020|publisher=[[Vice News]]}}</ref><ref name=\":0\"/><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.langleyadvance.com/federalelection/323015761.html|title=Langley post-secondary student runs as Libertarian|last=Claxton|first=Matthew|date=26 August 2015|newspaper=Langley Advance|access-date=30 October 2016|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161031150933/http://www.langleyadvance.com/federalelection/323015761.html|archivedate=31 October 2016}}</ref> Southern said she dropped out because \"it was a waste of money to pay for knowledge she could obtain on her own.\"<ref name=\"V\"/>\n\nOn January 29, 2020, Southern posted on Instagram announcing that, since her leaving public life, she had married and given birth to a son, while also announcing a desire to keep her family life private.<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/B76_b_QgoCu/</ref>\n\n==Political career==\nIn 2015, Southern was a candidate in the [[2015 Canadian federal election]] representing the [[Libertarian Party of Canada|Libertarian Party]] in the [[Electoral district (Canada)|district]] of [[Langley\u2014Aldergrove]].<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/irl/lauren-southern-libertarian/|title=Meet the Canadian college student who's about to be the next enemy of the feminist movement|last=Kabas|first=Marisa|date=15 June 2015|work=[[The Daily Dot]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150728105328/http://www.dailydot.com/lifestyle/lauren-southern-libertarian/|archivedate=28 July 2015}}</ref> She was briefly removed by the party as a candidate, but was eventually reinstated with support from ''[[Breitbart News]]'' and [[The Rebel Media]].<ref name=\"Claxton2017\"/> The election was won by [[Conservative Party of Canada|Conservative]] candidate [[Mark Warawa]]. Southern finished last, having received 535 votes, or 0.9% of the total.<ref>{{cite web|title=Official Voting Results {{!}} British Columbia, Langley\u2014Aldergrove {{!}} Forty-second General Election, 2015|url=http://www.elections.ca/res/rep/off/ovr2015app/41/9800e.html|website=www.elections.ca|accessdate=13 December 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815205225/http://elections.ca/res/rep/off/ovr2015app/41/9800e.html|archivedate=15 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Activism==\nIn June 2015, while reporting on the [[Vancouver]] [[SlutWalk]] for The Rebel Media, Southern's cameraman was shoved and Southern's protest sign stating \"There Is No Rape Culture In The West\" was torn up.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.themarysue.com/the-triggering-is-dumb/|title=Internet Jerks Pledge to Make Internet Even Worse in #TheTriggering|last=Lachenal|first=Jessica|date=9 March 2016|website=[[The Mary Sue]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923230529/http://www.themarysue.com/the-triggering-is-dumb|archivedate=23 September 2016|access-date=3 September 2016}}</ref><ref>Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Cloutier: ''[http://www.tvqc.com/2015/06/lauren-southern-troll-la-slutwalk-en-disant-il-ny-a-pas-de-culture-du-viol-en-occident Lauren Southern troll la SlutWalk]'' {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701003911/http://www.tvqc.com/2015/06/lauren-southern-troll-la-slutwalk-en-disant-il-ny-a-pas-de-culture-du-viol-en-occident|date=1 July 2017}}, TVQC, 14 June 2015.{{in lang|fr}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2016, a protester in Vancouver poured an unknown liquid over Southern's head while she was engaging with LGBTQ protesters at a rally in Vancouver, arguing for [[gender binary|two human genders]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/activist-pours-bottle-of-urine-on-rebel-reporter-during-anti-fascist-in-vancouver|title=Activist accused of pouring bottle of urine on Rebel reporter during 'anti-fascist' rally in Vancouver|last=Raptis|first=Mike|date=7 March 2016|work=[[National Post]]|access-date=21 May 2016|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200124035423/https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/activist-pours-bottle-of-urine-on-rebel-reporter-during-anti-fascist-in-vancouver|archive-date=24 January 2020|agency=[[Postmedia News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://torontosun.com/2016/03/07/activist-pours-urine-onto-reporters-head/wcm/691fca59-2582-4724-a229-678e70549768|title=Activist pours urine onto Rebel reporter's head|last=Raptis|first=Mike|date=7 March 2016|work=[[The Province]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180606012807/http://torontosun.com/2016/03/07/activist-pours-urine-onto-reporters-head/wcm/691fca59-2582-4724-a229-678e70549768|archive-date=6 June 2018|via=the ''[[Toronto Sun]]''|access-date=24 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://au.news.yahoo.com/a/31043202/protester-pours-urine-on-journalist-for-hateful-comments|title=Protester pours urine on journalist for 'hateful' comments|last=Christian|first=Natasha|date=8 March 2016|work=[[Yahoo! News]]|access-date=21 May 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160611014851/https://au.news.yahoo.com/a/31043202/protester-pours-urine-on-journalist-for-hateful-comments|archivedate=11 June 2016|publisher=[[Yahoo7]]}}</ref>\n\nSouthern was mistakenly suspended from [[Facebook]], having criticized the site for banning several conservative commentators. She later received an email apology from Facebook saying the suspension was an \"error\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-troll-booth-1464026102|title=The Troll Booth|last=Taranto|first=James|date=23 May 2016|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|access-date=3 September 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20160523181218/http://www.wsj.com/articles/the-troll-booth-1464026102|archivedate=23 May 2016|url-access=subscription}}</ref><!-- Please discuss on the talkpage before editing this section -->\n\nIn October 2016, Southern had her gender legally changed to male as part of a video produced for The Rebel Media to show the ease of Ontario's new gender ID laws.<ref name=\"Trans video\">{{cite web|url=https://www.therebel.media/lauren_southern_becomes_a_man|title=Lauren Southern Becomes a Man!|last=Southern|first=Lauren|date=3 October 2016|publisher=[[The Rebel Media]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023195624/http://www.therebel.media/lauren_southern_becomes_a_man|archivedate=23 October 2016|accessdate=28 October 2016}}</ref><!-- Please discuss on the talkpage before editing this section --><ref>Tamara Wernli: ''[http://bazonline.ch/leben/gesellschaft/Total-durchgeknallt/story/28206664 Total durchgeknallt] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325100139/http://bazonline.ch/leben/gesellschaft/total-durchgeknallt/story/28206664|date=25 March 2017}}'' (in German). In: [[Basler Zeitung]], 1 December 2016.</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Southern authored and self-published ''Barbarians: How Baby Boomers, Immigrants, and Islam Screwed My Generation''.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Southern|first1=Lauren|title=Barbarians: How Baby Boomers, Immigrants, and Islam Screwed My Generation|publisher=[[CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform]]|date=21 December 2016|ISBN=978-1541136946}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hopenothate.org.uk/2018/03/14/brittany-pettibone-lauren-southern-not-conservative-activists-journalists/|title=Brittany Pettibone and Lauren Southern Are Not \"Conservative\" Activists or \"Journalists\"|date=14 March 2018|publisher=[[Hope Not Hate]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621163917/https://www.hopenothate.org.uk/2018/03/14/brittany-pettibone-lauren-southern-not-conservative-activists-journalists/|archive-date=21 June 2019|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2017, Southern posted to [[Twitter]] incorrect rumours from the website [[4chan]] that the [[Quebec City mosque shooting]] had been carried out by Syrian refugees; she later deleted those tweets.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/twitter-and-the-mosque-shooting-a-tale-of-fake-news-and-bias/|title=Twitter, the mosque shooting, fake news and bias|last=Hutchins|first=Aaron|date=30 January 2017|work=[[Maclean's]]|access-date=21 June 2017|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170621032208/http://www.macleans.ca/news/canada/twitter-and-the-mosque-shooting-a-tale-of-fake-news-and-bias|archive-date=21 June 2017}}</ref> In March 2017, Southern announced she would be leaving The Rebel Media to become an independent journalist.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=18ZRJ0D6zPE|title=Going Independent|date=9 March 2017|last=Southern|first=Lauren|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310201035/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=18ZRJ0D6zPE|archivedate=10 March 2017|url-status=live|via=YouTube}}</ref> In the same month, she gained access to [[White House]] press briefings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mediamatters.org/alex-jones/meet-lauren-southern-latest-alt-right-media-troll-gain-access-white-house-press-briefing|title=Meet Lauren Southern, The Latest \"Alt-Right\" Media Troll To Gain Access To The White House Press Briefing|last=L\u00f3pez G.|first=Christina|date=14 March 2017|publisher=[[Media Matters for America]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200106064923/https://www.mediamatters.org/alex-jones/meet-lauren-southern-latest-alt-right-media-troll-gain-access-white-house-press-briefing|archive-date=6 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://forward.com/news/366179/trumps-white-house-welcomes-5-new-far-right-figures/|title=Trump\u2019s White House Welcomes 5 New Far-Right Figures|last=Kestenbaum|first=Sam|date=15 March 2017|work=[[The Forward]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190807120435/https://forward.com/news/366179/trumps-white-house-welcomes-5-new-far-right-figures/|archive-date=7 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, Southern was one of several scheduled speakers at a [[Patriots' Day]] rally in [[Berkeley, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalobserver.com/2017/04/26/news/canadian-connection-extremist-fringe-inside-berkeley-violence|title=Exclusive: The Canadian extremists inside the Berkeley violence|last1=Robb|first1=Amanda|date=26 April 2017|website=[[National Observer (Canada)|National Observer]]|publisher=[[Observer Media Group]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://archive.today/20170618195930/http://www.nationalobserver.com/2017/04/26/news/canadian-connection-extremist-fringe-inside-berkeley-violence|archivedate=18 June 2017|accessdate=13 March 2018|quote=On April 15, American activists, many of whom support closed U.S. borders, held a \"Patriots Day\" rally in Berkeley, California. One of the marquee speakers was Lauren Southern, a Canadian.}}</ref> The rally led to [[2017 Berkeley protests#April 15|a riot]] between pro-Trump demonstrators and anti-Trump counter-protesters.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/berkeley-braces-for-latest-face-off-between-trump-supporters-detractors/15620/|title=Clashes Break Out at Opposing Rallies in Berkeley|last=Mahbubani|first=Rhea|date=15 April 2017|access-date=15 April 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170416034700/http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Berkeley-Braces-for-Latest-Face-Off-Between-Trump-Supporters-Detractors-419535563.html|archivedate=16 April 2017|publisher=[[NBC Bay Area]]|last2=Smith|first2=Christie}}</ref>\n\n===Opposition to NGOs, refugees, and migration===\nIn May 2017, Southern took part in an attempt organized by the Identitarian group ''[[Les Identitaires#G.C3.A9n.C3.A9ration Identitaire|G\u00e9n\u00e9ration identitare]]'' to block the passage of an NGO ship, the [[Aquarius (NGO ship)|''Aquarius'']] (co-owned by SOS Mediterran\u00e9e and by [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res|Doctors without Borders]]), which was leaving [[Sicily]] to start a search-and-rescue mission for ship-wrecked refugees and migrants off the shores of Northern Africa.<ref name=\"Claxton2017\" /> Claiming that the goal of the activists \"was to stop an empty boat from going down to Libya and filling up with illegal migrants\", Southern was briefly detained by the [[Italian Coast Guard]]. NGO ships often rescue migrants and refugees, who disembark from Libyan shores on unsafe makeshift rafts, and bring them to Sicily.<ref name=\"Claxton2017\" /><ref>Claudio Cartaldo: [http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cronache/migranti-blitz-contro-long-identiatari-bloccano-nave-che-va-1396686.html Migranti, blitz contro l'Ong] {{webarchive|url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170607125448/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cronache/migranti-blitz-contro-long-identiatari-bloccano-nave-che-va-1396686.html|date= 7 June 2017}} (in Italian). In: ''[[il Giornale]]'', 13 May 2017.</ref> Regarding her actions, Southern stated: \"if the politicians won't stop the boats, we'll stop the boats.\"<ref name=\"Claxton2017\"/>\n\nSouthern supported similar actions by Defend Europe, which chartered a vessel to track and stop what it called collusion between NGOs and human traffickers. In July 2017, Southern revealed that [[Patreon]] had deleted her account citing concerns about her \"raising funds in order to take part in activities that are likely to cause loss of life\".<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rtImwK5TI4g|title=PATREON BANNED MY ACCOUNT??|date=21 July 2017|last=Southern|first=Lauren|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723023740/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rtImwK5TI4g|archivedate=23 July 2017|url-status=live|via=YouTube}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/layer8/patreon-antifa-altright-igd-lauren-southern/|title=How Patreon stepped into a war between Antifa and the alt-right|last=Gilmour|first=David|date=8 August 2017|website=[[The Daily Dot]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20170809173106/https://www.dailydot.com/layer8/patreon-antifa-altright-igd-lauren-southern/|archive-date=9 August 2017|access-date=23 January 2020}}</ref> Southern denied these allegations, stating that Defend Europe's actions were likely to save lives and that none of her funding went towards the group.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite news|last1=Gordon|first1=Graeme|title=Why Lauren Southern Got Banned From Patreon|url=http://www.canadalandshow.com/lauren-southern-banned-by-patreon|accessdate= 17 August 2017|work= Canadaland|date=27 July 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818133356/http://www.canadalandshow.com/lauren-southern-banned-by-patreon|archivedate=18 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2018, Southern released a video that appeared to show an NGO worker admitting that she had coached asylum seekers on how to speak to immigration officials in order to gain refugee status. ''[[BuzzFeed News]]'' reported that a UNHCR spokesperson said: \"Greece has rigorous asylum procedures in place, within a robust legal framework.\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/rosebuchanan/far-right-youtube-lauen-southern-secret-recording-refugees|title=A Far-Right YouTuber Has Been Secretly Recording NGO Workers Inside One Of Europe\u2019s Worst Refugee Camps|last1=Buchanan|first1=Rose Troup|date=13 November 2018|work=[[BuzzFeed News]]|accessdate=26 May 2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190614083518/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/rosebuchanan/far-right-youtube-lauen-southern-secret-recording-refugees|archive-date=14 June 2019|last2=Broderick|first2=Ryan}}</ref> In May 2019, Southern released a YouTube documentary, ''Borderless'', about the refugee and migrant crisis. The film was temporarily taken down by YouTube.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dougherty |first1=Michael Brendan |title=Silicon Valley, America\u2019s De Facto Censor |url=https://www.nationalreview.com/2019/05/silicon-valley-social-media-companies-censors/ |accessdate=1 June 2019 |work=National Review |date=May 30, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZQ_fz9EW5Iw|first=Lauren|last=Southern|title=Borderless (2019) Official Documentary|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=10 June 2019}}</ref>{{better source|date=June 2019}}\n\n===Ban on entering the United Kingdom===\nIn February 2018, Southern, along with Brittany Pettibone and Caolan Robertson, distributed flyers in the English town of [[Luton]] describing [[Allah]] as \"gay\".<ref name=\"BBC_Entry\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-43393035|title=Why 3 anti-Islam activists were refused entry to the UK|date=14 March 2018|accessdate=3 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180318142459/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-43393035|archivedate=18 March 2018|publisher=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2018, Southern, Pettibone, and Identitarian activist [[Martin Sellner]] were all denied entry to the United Kingdom.<ref name=\"Bachmann\">{{cite news|title=Lutz Bachmann: Founder of far-right anti-Islam group Pegida barred from entry to UK and deported|work=[[The Independent]]|first=Maya|last=Oppenheim|date=18 March 2018|accessdate=17 April 2018|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/lutz-bachmann-pegida-detained-stansted-deported-a8262131.html|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180319180728/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/lutz-bachmann-pegida-detained-stansted-deported-a8262131.html|archivedate=19 March 2018}}</ref> Southern was also questioned under the Schedule 7 of the [[Terrorism Act 2000]].<ref name=\"BBC_Entry\"/> Her denial of entry was due to her intentions during her March visit<ref name=NationalPost/> and on the same grounds as Pettibone and Sellner.<ref name=\"BBC_Entry\"/><ref name=\"indBan\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/lauren-southern-far-right-canada-racist-calais-detain-uk-ban-enter-visa-a8254116.html|title=Far-right Canadian activist detained in Calais and banned from entering UK|last1=Oppenheim|first1=Maya|date=13 March 2018|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=2 April 2019|url-status=live|archive-url=https://archive.today/20180318204635/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/lauren-southern-far-right-canada-racist-calais-detain-uk-ban-enter-visa-a8254116.html|archive-date=18 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-security-deportations/british-authorities-ban-three-foreign-right-wing-activists-idUSKCN1GO2LN|title=British authorities ban three foreign right-wing activists|last=Hosenball|first=Mark|date=12 March 2018|accessdate=3 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180320082821/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-security-deportations/british-authorities-ban-three-foreign-right-wing-activists-idUSKCN1GO2LN|archivedate=20 March 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref><ref name=\"nigel_farage\">{{cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/nigel-farage-defends-right-wing-canadian-activist-lauren-southern-who-was-barred-from-uk-a3790816.html|title=Lauren Southern defended by Nigel Farage after right wing Canadian activist was barred from UK|last=Grafton-Green|first=Patrick|date=15 March 2018|newspaper=[[Evening Standard]]|accessdate=23 July 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621231305/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/nigel-farage-defends-right-wing-canadian-activist-lauren-southern-who-was-barred-from-uk-a3790816.html|archive-date=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2018 Australian tour===\nShortly before a planned speaking tour of Australia in July 2018, Australia's [[Department of Home Affairs (Australia)|Department of Home Affairs]] denied Lauren Southern an Electronic Travel Authority visa, saying it was \"not a working visa\".<ref name=\"workvisa\">{{cite news|title=Visa approved for Canadian who warns Australian way of life is under threat|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/visa-approved-for-canadian-who-warns-australian-way-of-life-is-under-threat|publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]]|accessdate=10 July 2018|date=10 July 2018}}</ref> She intended to charge $79 for a basic ticket and up to $749 for an \"intimate dinner\".<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chung|first1=Frank|title=Australian government declines visa for right-wing activist Lauren Southern ahead of speaking tour|url=https://www.news.com.au/finance/business/media/australian-government-declines-visa-for-rightwing-activist-lauren-southern-ahead-of-speaking-tour/news-story/7b9a15a56981e4508e5305887f85c0e3|accessdate=19 February 2019|work=news.com.au|date=10 July 2018}}</ref> The Australian government allowed her to enter the country once she had the correct visa.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news.com.au/finance/business/media/rightwing-activist-lauren-southerns-australian-visa-approved-after-unusually-prolonged-process/news-story/5e3611992c9edfeb2c65b9db47d901d0|title=Lauren Southern's Australian visa approved after all|website=www.news.com.au}}</ref> Arriving at [[Brisbane]] airport, she was wearing an \"[[It's OK to be white]]\" shirt.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/it-s-ok-to-be-white-far-right-youtuber-lauren-southern-lands-in-australia-20180714-p4zrgq.html|title='It's OK to be white': Far right YouTuber Lauren Southern lands in Australia|first=Pallavi|last=Singhal|date=14 July 2018|website=The Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.news.com.au/finance/business/media/rightwing-activist-lauren-southern-touches-down-in-brisbane-wearing-its-okay-to-be-white-tshirt/news-story/d750c1b70a5e969ad4190540909ac75d|title=Lauren Southern lands in Brisbane wearing \u2018It\u2019s okay to be white\u2019 T-shirt|website=News.com.au}}</ref>\n\nWhen she asked people on the street in [[Melbourne]] \"Should we kill Lauren Southern?\", many had never heard of her.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u2018You\u2019re not welcome\u2019: Southern\u2019s run-in with police |url=https://www.qt.com.au/news/youre-not-welcome-southerns-runin-with-sydney-poli/3478516/ |accessdate=1 August 2018 |newspaper=Queensland Times |date=28 July 2018}}</ref> A speaking event in Melbourne was opposed by more than 100 protestors.<ref name=\"Melbourne_protests\">{{cite news |title=Protesters disrupt Lauren Southern event in Melbourne |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/protesters-disrupt-lauren-southern-event-in-melbourne |publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]] |accessdate=31 July 2018 |date=20 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nThere were no protestors at her event in [[Sydney]], where ticket holders were notified of the venue by receiving a text on the day.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Douglas |title=Far-right Canadian duo\u2019s vile rampage against Aboriginal culture at Sydney event |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2017/07/30/far-right-canadian-duos-vile-rampage-against-aboriginal-culture-sydney-event |accessdate=1 August 2018 |publisher=sbs.com.au |date=30 July 2018}}</ref> The Sydney event included a $200 meet-and-greet, a $500 VIP meet-and-greet and a $750 dinner.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kinsella |first1=Luke |title=What I learnt about the far right from Lauren Southern |url=https://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/real-life/true-stories/what-i-learnt-about-the-far-right-from-lauren-southern/news-story/0443ce7a7a09dc8431776f469b34ae0d |accessdate=1 August 2018 |work=news.com.au |date=30 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Brisbane]], Southern mentioned bombing the Australian city of [[Melbourne]], quoting the [[Bible]], as a joke.<ref name=\"not_yet_joke\">{{cite news|title=Lauren Southern insults Melbourne, city fires back|url=https://www.news.com.au/national/victoria/news/lauren-southern-insults-melbourne-city-fires-back/news-story/820aeccdc9e8f0ddf936b878c195a81a|accessdate=14 August 2018|work=News.com.au|date=4 August 2018}}</ref> She was opposed by around 60 protesters.<ref name=\"Brisbane_protests\">{{cite news |last1=Chirgwin|first1=Sophie|title=Alt right activist Lauren Southern targeted in Brisbane|url=https://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/alt-right-activist-lauren-southern-targeted-in-brisbane/news-story/8ba241e85a0a8dbdfe95cededab53406|accessdate=3 August 2018|newspaper=The Courier Mail|date=30 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n===2018 New Zealand tour===\nIn July 2018, Southern applied for a travel visa to visit [[New Zealand]] for a speaking tour with Canadian podcaster and YouTuber [[Stefan Molyneux]]. [[Minister of Immigration (New Zealand)|Immigration Minister]] [[Iain Lees-Galloway]] described their views as \"repugnant\", but said they met immigration character requirements and cleared their entry.<ref name=\"Satherley\">{{cite news|last1=Satherley|first1=Dan|title=Protests outside Lauren Southern speaking gig in Melbourne|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2018/07/protests-outside-lauren-southern-speaking-gig-in-melbourne.html|accessdate=21 July 2018|publisher=[[Newshub]]|date=21 July 2018}}</ref> The pair had not secured a venue, as [[Auckland Council]] had cancelled their initial booking, citing health and safety concerns.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Fonseka|first1=Dileepa|title=Lauren Southern and Stefan Molyneux have 'visas in hand' and will come to NZ, organiser says|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/105625016/Lauren-Southern-and-Stefan-Molyneux-have-visas-in-hand-and-will-come-to-NZ-organiser-says|accessdate=20 July 2018|agency=Stuff.co.nz|publisher=Auckland Now|date=20 July 2018}}</ref> The pair briefly cancelled and then resumed the tour over difficulties with the venue.<ref>{{cite news |title=Right-wing Canadian speakers' visit canned, legal action on back burner |last1=Niall |first1=Todd |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/105744525/rightwing-canadian-speakers-visit-canned-legal-action-on-back-burner | date=25 July 2018 |accessdate=25 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Canadian far-right speakers Lauren Southern, Stefan Molyneux coming to New Zealand after securing Auckland speaking venue|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/canadian-far-right-speakers-lauren-southern-stefan-molyneux-coming-new-zealand-after-securing-auckland-speaking-venue|accessdate=26 July 2018|publisher=[[1 News]]|date=26 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Todd|first1=Niall|title=Canadian Right-wing speakers' Auckland tour is on, with a new venue|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/105780606/canadian-rightwing-speakers-auckland-tour-is-on-with-a-new-venue|accessdate=26 July 2018|agency=Stuff.co.nz|publisher=AucklandNow|date=26 July 2018}}</ref> The subsequent booking of a private venue was revoked by its owners.<ref name=\"The_minute_I_heard_who_it_was_I_cancelled\">{{cite news |last1=Truebridge |first1=Nick |first2=Niall |last2=Todd |title=Auckland's Powerstation owner apologises for booking controversial speakers |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/106002242/aucklands-powerstation-owner-apologises-for-booking-controversial-speakers |accessdate=3 August 2018 |work=[[Stuff.co.nz]] |date=3 August 2018}}</ref> In retaliation, their venue was vandalised.<ref name=vandalised>{{cite news |title=Powerstation vandalised after cancelling Lauren Southern and Stefan Molyneux event |url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2018/08/powerstation-vandalised-after-cancelling-lauren-southern-and-stefan-molyneux-event.html |accessdate=6 August 2018 |publisher=[[Newshub]] |date=6 August 2018}}</ref> The failure to find a venue was celebrated by around 1,000 protestors, who said the planned event had nothing to do with freedom of speech. [[Prime Minister of New Zealand|Prime Minister]] [[Jacinda Ardern]] said Southern's views \"are not those that are shared by this country\".<ref name=\"NZ_Hostile_to_Southern\">{{cite news |last1=Ensor |first1=Jamie |last2=Macdonald |first2=Laura |title=NZ 'hostile' to views of Lauren Southern and Stefan Molyneux - Jacinda Arden |url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2018/08/nz-hostile-to-views-of-lauren-southern-and-stefan-molyneux-jacinda-arden.html |accessdate=4 August 2018 |publisher=[[Newshub]] |date=4 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, the [[Mayor of Auckland]] [[Phil Goff]] tweeted that Council venues should not be used to \"stir up ethnic or religious tensions\", and that \"we've got no obligation at all\" to provide a venue for hate speech.<ref name=radionz/><ref>{{cite news|title=Controversial Canadian speaker denied visa as Auckland agency cancels booking|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/auckland/105302179/controversial-canadian-speaker-denied-visa-as-auckland-agency-cancels-booking|newspaper=Stuff|date=6 July 2018|accessdate=29 September 2018}}</ref> For agreeing with the cancellation, an MP received threats of violence.<ref name=\"Degrading_Messages_of_a_Sexual_Nature_from_Lauren_Southern_fans\">{{cite news |title=Green Party co-leader Marama Davidson receives death threats |url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/politics/2018/07/green-party-co-leader-marama-davidson-receives-death-threats.html |accessdate=4 August 2018 |publisher=[[Newshub]] |date=8 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nT\u0101maki Anti Fascist Action spokesperson Sina Brown-Davis said her group feared \"dehumanising depictions of indigenous people\" in New Zealand.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Theunissen |first1=Matthew |title=Most read: Fear controversial far-right pair\u2019s speech will incite racism: \u2018They were mocking Aboriginal culture' |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/most-read-fear-controversial-far-right-pair-s-speech-incite-racism-they-were-mocking-aboriginal-culture |accessdate=3 August 2018 |publisher=[[1 News]] |date=2 August 2018}}</ref> Molyneux had called Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people \"the lowest rung of civilisation\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Smith |first1=Douglas |title=Far-right Canadian duo\u2019s vile rampage against Aboriginal culture at Sydney event |url=https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/article/2017/07/30/far-right-canadian-duos-vile-rampage-against-aboriginal-culture-sydney-event |accessdate=3 August 2018 |publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service|SBS]] |date=30 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nPrime Minister Jacinda Ardern said New Zealand is \"hostile\" to the views of the speakers and \"I think you'll see from the reaction they've had from New Zealanders that their views are not those that are shared by this country, and I'm quite proud of that\".<ref name=\"NZ_Hostile_to_Southern\"/> [[Green Party of Aotearoa New Zealand|Green Party]] co-leader [[Marama Davidson]] added \"Aotearoa does not stand for your messages of racism, hatred and especially white supremacy\".<ref name=\"Right_Of_Stalin\">{{cite news |title=\"Hope NZ enjoys shariah\" - Alt-right speakers' agent responds to having their Auckland event at The Powerstation cancelled last-minute |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/hope-nz-enjoys-shariah-alt-right-speakers-agent-responds-having-their-auckland-event-powerstation-cancelled-last-minute |accessdate=4 August 2018 |publisher=[[1 News]] |date=4 August 2018}}</ref> [[Minister of Justice (New Zealand)|Justice Minister]] [[Andrew Little (New Zealand politician)|Andrew Little]] said the speakers \"clearly have misled people\" in trying to secure the venue.<ref name=misled>{{cite news |url=https://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?objectid=12101189 |title=Andrew Little happy 'insidious' alt-right pair leaving the country as bomb threat claim emerges |newspaper=[[The New Zealand Herald|NZ Herald]] |first=David |last=Fisher |date=4 August 2018 |accessdate=6 August 2018}}</ref> TV personality Te Hamua Nikora said the pair were against multiculturalism, unlike New Zealand.<ref name=\"How_to_travel_the_world_for_free\">{{cite news |title=Watch: Canadian far-right speakers blame threats of violence amounting to 'straight up terrorism' for Auckland event cancellation |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/watch-canadian-far-right-speakers-blame-threats-violence-amounting-straight-up-terrorism-auckland-event-cancellation |accessdate=3 August 2018 |publisher=[[1 News]] |date=3 August 2018}}</ref> The minimum ticket price for the cancelled Auckland event was $99.<ref name=\"tickets_min_99_NZD\">{{cite news |title=Auckland venue cancels controversial far-right Canadian pair's speaking event |url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/auckland-venue-cancels-controversial-far-right-canadian-pairs-speaking-event |accessdate=3 August 2018 |publisher=[[1 News]] |date=3 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Retirement===\nOn June 2, 2019, Southern announced her retirement from political activism in her website. She stated that her reasons for leaving were that she needed to move on and find fulfillment in a more private capacity.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://laurensouthern.net/a-new-chapter/ |title=A New Chapter |last=Southern |first=Lauren |date=2019-06-02 |accessdate=2019-06-11 }}</ref>\n\n==Views==\nSouthern has been widely described as [[alt-right]],{{efn|name=alt-right bundle| Sources describing her as \"alt-right\" include:\n*{{Cite news|last=Wildman|first=Sarah|url=https://www.vox.com/platform/amp/world/2017/7/6/15804196/generation-identity-identitarians-alt-right-migration-islam-refugees-europe|title=A European alt-right group wants to take to the sea to stop rescuers from saving migrants |work=Vox|access-date=6 July 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706150831/https://www.vox.com/platform/amp/world/2017/7/6/15804196/generation-identity-identitarians-alt-right-migration-islam-refugees-europe|archivedate=6 July 2017}}\n*{{Cite news|last=Khandakar|first=Tamara|url=https://news.vice.com/story/lauren-southern-is-the-alt-rights-not-so-secret-weapon|title=Lauren Southern is the alt-right's not-so-secret weapon|access-date=6 July 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170716192152/https://news.vice.com/story/lauren-southern-is-the-alt-rights-not-so-secret-weapon|archivedate=16 July 2017}}\n*{{Cite news|last=Neiwert|first=David|url=https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2017/04/17/far-right-descends-berkeley-free-speech-and-planned-violence|title=The Far Right Descends on Berkeley for 'Free Speech' and Planned Violence|work=Hatewatch|publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center|access-date=27 July 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817211931/https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2017/04/17/far-right-descends-berkeley-free-speech-and-planned-violence|archivedate=17 August 2017}}\n*{{cite news |title=Alt-right activist Lauren Southern's visa rejected on eve of Australian tour |url=https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/altright-activist-lauren-southerns-visa-rejected-on-eve-of-australian-tour/news-story/3a6a2cc36a0fcec59da5b1bebfcfed6a |accessdate=9 July 2018 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)]] |date=9 July 2018 |language=en}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Warren |first1=James |title=How women of the alt-right are attacked viciously \u2014 by the men of the alt-right |url=https://www.poynter.org/news/how-women-alt-right-are-attacked-viciously-men-alt-right |accessdate=9 July 2018 |work=Poynter |date=7 December 2017 |language=en}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Mortimer|first1=Caroline|title=Far-right activists stopped as they try to block refugee rescue in the Mediterranean|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/anti-immigrant-ship-far-right-refugee-boats-stopped-suez-canal-c-star-defend-europe-islamophobic-a7851341.html|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=The Independent|date=20 July 2017}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Porter|first1=Tom|title=A U.S. alt-right media personality was among a group of activists denied entry to the U.K.|url=http://www.newsweek.com/us-blogger-among-three-alt-right-activists-denied-entry-uk-840782|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=Newsweek|date=12 March 2018|language=en}}\n* {{Cite web|page=14|url=http://politicalcapital.hu/pc-admin/source/documents/Laruelle_Rivera_Collusion_or_Homegrown_Collaboration.pdf|first=Marlene|last=Laruelle|title=Collusion or Homegrown Collaboration? Connections between German Far Right and Russia|date=April 2019|authorlink=Marlene Laruelle|first2=Ellen|last2=Rivera|publisher=Political Capital Policy Research and Consulting Institute}}\n}} [[far-right]]{{efn|name=far-right bundle| Sources describing her as \"far-right\" include:\n*{{cite news|last1=Gordon|first1=Graeme|title=Why Lauren Southern Got Banned From Patreon|url=http://www.canadalandshow.com/lauren-southern-banned-by-patreon|accessdate=17 August 2017|work=Canadaland|date=27 July 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818133356/http://www.canadalandshow.com/lauren-southern-banned-by-patreon/|archivedate=18 August 2017}}\n*{{cite news |last1=Wilson |first1=Jason |title=White farmers: how a far-right idea was planted in Donald Trump's mind |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/aug/23/white-farmers-trump-south-africa-tucker-carlson-far-right-influence |accessdate=10 November 2018 |agency=The Guardian |date=24 August 2018}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Baidawi|first1=Adam|title=South Africa Says Australia Retracted Claim of 'Persecuted' White Farmers|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/03/world/australia/south-africa-white-farmers.html|accessdate=16 April 2018|work=The New York Times|date=3 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180416134948/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/03/world/australia/south-africa-white-farmers.html|archivedate=16 April 2018}}\n*{{cite news|title=Canadian far-right activist Lauren Southern barred from Britain for anti-Muslim views|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/far-right-figures-say-they-were-deported-from-britain|accessdate=16 April 2018|work=National Post|date=12 March 2018}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Oppenheim|first1=Maya|title=Far-right Canadian activist detained in Calais and banned from entering UK|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/lauren-southern-far-right-canada-racist-calais-detain-uk-ban-enter-visa-a8254116.html|accessdate=16 April 2018|work=The Independent|date=13 March 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180315144150/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/lauren-southern-far-right-canada-racist-calais-detain-uk-ban-enter-visa-a8254116.html|archivedate=15 March 2018}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Maxwell|first1=Tani|title='There's no one for right-wingers to pick a fight with': The far right is struggling to sustain interest in its social media platforms|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/far-right-tech-platforms-gab-youtube-bitchute-2017-9|accessdate=16 April 2018|work=Business Insider|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180131084729/http://www.businessinsider.com/far-right-tech-platforms-gab-youtube-bitchute-2017-9|archivedate=31 January 2018}}\n}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-05-04/trump-retweets-far-right-youtube-star-in-attack-on-social-media|title=Trump Retweets Far-Right YouTube Star in Attack on Social Media|date=2019|website=Bloomberg|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190504173259/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-05-04/trump-retweets-far-right-youtube-star-in-attack-on-social-media|archive-date=4 May 2019|url-status=live|access-date=4 May 2019}}</ref> and [[Right-wing politics|right-wing]].{{efn|name=right wing bundle|Sources describing her as \"right-wing\" include:\n*{{cite news|last1=Shaw|first1=Adam|title=Right-wing journalist Lauren Southern denied entry to UK, purportedly over criticism of Islam|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2018/03/12/right-wing-journalist-lauren-southern-denied-entry-to-uk-purportedly-over-criticism-islam.html|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=Fox News|date=12 March 2018}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Hosenball|first1=Mark|title=British authorities ban three foreign right-wing activists|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-britain-security-deportations/british-authorities-ban-three-foreign-right-wing-activists-idUSKCN1GO2LN|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=Reuters|date=12 March 2018}}\n*{{cite news|last1=Farrell|first1=Jeff|title=Anti-immigrant ship trying to block refugees from crossing Mediterranean has funding cancelled|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/defend-europe-finding-patreon-refugee-boats-mediterranean-sea-c-star-migrants-right-wing-ngo-rescue-a7891946.html|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=The Independent|date=14 August 2017}}\n}} She rejects the label \"alt-right\". The [[Southern Poverty Law Center]] has described Southern's videos as [[antifeminist]], xenophobic, [[Islamophobic]] and borderline [[white nationalist]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shaw|first1=Adam|title=Right-wing journalist Lauren Southern denied entry to UK, purportedly over criticism of Islam|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2018/03/12/right-wing-journalist-lauren-southern-denied-entry-to-uk-purportedly-over-criticism-islam.html|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=Fox News|date=12 March 2018}}</ref> She is [[anti-multiculturalism|anti-multicultural]] and has called the [[Black Lives Matter]] movement a \"terrorist organisation\".<ref name=newshub_views>{{cite news |url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/new-zealand/2018/07/explainer-what-do-far-right-canadian-speakers-stefan-molyneux-and-lauren-southern-believe.html |title=Explainer: What do far-right Canadian speakers Stefan Molyneux and Lauren Southern believe? |publisher=[[Newshub]] |date=20 July 2018 |accessdate=6 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Gender===\nSouthern said transgender people have a \"genuine delusion\" adding \"It\u2019s [[body dysmorphia]] and that is a mental illness\".<ref name=\"anti_trans\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/business/media/victoria-police-charge-lauren-southern/news-story/9986324084f649beaa9cc568e51523e0|title=Women \u2018not developed\u2019 to be CEOs, activist Lauren Southern says|newspaper=[[The Australian]]|date=20 July 2018|first=Rhian|last=Deutrom}}</ref> She criticised legal recognition for changing one's gender, because people doing so might be \"dishonest\".<ref name=newshub_views/>\n\nSouthern has spoken in opposition to [[feminism]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/it-s-ok-to-be-white-far-right-youtuber-lauren-southern-lands-in-australia-20180714-p4zrgq.html |title='It's OK to be white': Far right speaker Lauren Southern lands in Australia |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=14 July 2018}}</ref> and has said that women are \"not psychologically developed to hold leadership positions\",<ref name=out/> and \"not going to be as great being CEOs\".<ref name=\"anti_trans\"/> In 2015 she attended [[SlutWalk]] and held a sign that read, \"There is no [[rape culture]] in the West.\"<ref name=\"V\"/> She also said that it was \"insane\" to focus on the issue.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/woman-holds-sign-at-feminist-rally-saying-there-is-no-rape-culture-in-the-west-10310370.html |title=Woman holds sign at feminist rally saying 'there is no rape culture in the West' |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=10 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Multiculturalism===\nSouthern is [[anti-multiculturalism|against multiculturalism]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tvnz.co.nz/one-news/new-zealand/most-read-fear-controversial-far-right-pair-s-speech-incite-racism-they-were-mocking-aboriginal-culture|title=Fear controversial far-right pair\u2019s speech will incite racism: \u2018They were mocking Aboriginal culture'|date=2 August 2018|publisher=[[TVNZ]]}}</ref> She has asked whether a multicultural society would require \"[[witch doctors]]\" at medical conferences,<ref name=misled/> and has claimed that \"multiculturalism will inevitably fail unless 50 per cent of the population believes in [[Western culture]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/business/media/lauren-southern-welcomed-by-altright-australian-twitter/news-story/9f9f7dd343668945a2ac196bbb864327|title=Lauren Southern in Australia: \u2018I feel zero shame whatsoever for being white\u2019 |date=13 July 2018|newspaper=[[The Australian]]}}</ref> ''[[New Matilda]]'' reported that the core message of her 2018 speaking tour of Australia was that \"multiculturalism doesn't work\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://newmatilda.com/2018/08/09/ok-right-careful-wish-lauren-southern/ |title=It\u2019s OK To Be Right, But Careful What You Wish For Lauren Southern |date=9 August 2018|publisher=[[New Matilda]]}}</ref> On the tour, she caused controversy for publicly criticizing an \"Asian only\" room-share advert that she had photographed and called it \"extremely tribalistic\".<ref name=\"segregation\" /> This was an attempt to highlight the supposed failure of multiculturalism, by suggesting that it produced a form of \"segregation\".<ref name=\"segregation\">{{cite web|url=https://www.news.com.au/finance/business/media/lauren-southern-stirs-up-controversy-sharing-asian-only-ad/news-story/c98f0c441a0197e28a801a9d8c4c290c|title=Lauren Southern stirs up controversy sharing \u2018Asian only\u2019 ad|date=26 July 2018|publisher=[[News Corp Australia]]}}</ref>\n\n===Race===\nSouthern has defended the American [[neo-Nazi]] [[Richard B. Spencer]], who had said \"Hail Trump\" in a speech at a white nationalist gathering, and had called for a \"peaceful\" ethnic cleansing of America. Southern has said \"Richard Spencer is not a white supremacist, he is a white nationalist. He believes in a [[white ethnostate]], he doesn\u2019t believe in whites being superior.\"<ref name=\"Claxton2017\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Koul |first1=Saachi |title=Hey, America, Now You Have Our Worst People. You're Welcome. |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/scaachikoul/hey-america-now-you-have-our-worst-people-youre-welcome |accessdate=30 August 2018 |work=BuzzFeed News |date=19 August 2017 |language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"kelley\">{{cite news |last1=Kelley |first1=Brendan Joel |title=Lauren Southern: The alt-right\u2019s Canadian dog whistler |url=https://www.splcenter.org/hatewatch/2017/11/07/lauren-southern-alt-right%E2%80%99s-canadian-dog-whistler |accessdate=30 August 2018 |work=Hatewatch |publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center |date=7 November 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nSouthern has been cited as a proponent of [[white genocide conspiracy theory]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/oceania/the-high-price-of-white-genocide-politics-for-australia-20180724-p4zt9k.html |title=The high price of 'white genocide' politics for Australia |newspaper=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |date=12 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Dearden |first1=Lizzie |title=New Zealand attack: How nonsensical white genocide conspiracy theory cited by alleged gunman is spreading poison around the world |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/australasia/new-zealand-christchurch-mosque-attack-white-genocide-conspiracy-theory-a8824671.html |accessdate=1 April 2019 |work=The Independent |date=16 March 2019}}</ref> In 2018, Southern produced a documentary called ''Farmlands'' which claimed that racially motivated farm attacks in South Africa may represent an impending genocide, a common talking point for white nationalists.<ref name=out>{{cite news|url=https://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/lauren-southern-protesters-out-to-disrupt-right-wing-commentators-event/news-story/5b7db1c243bf7df639f535561679a36f|title=Lauren Southern: protesters out to disrupt right wing commentator\u2019s event|newspaper=[[The Australian]]|date=20 July 2018|first=Rebecca|last=Urban}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Baidawi|first1=Adam|title=South Africa Says Australia Retracted Claim of 'Persecuted' White Farmers|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/03/world/australia/south-africa-white-farmers.html|accessdate=9 May 2018|work=The New York Times|date=3 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/8/23/17772056/south-africa-trump-tweet-afriforum |title=Trump\u2019s tweet echoing white nationalist propaganda about South African farmers, explained |date=23 August 2018 |work=[[Salon (website)]]}}</ref> While producing the documentary, Southern worked with [[Unite the Right rally|Charlottesville Unite the Right rally]] attendee Simon Roche,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnn.com/interactive/2018/11/africa/south-africa-suidlanders-intl |title=They're prepping for a race war. And they see Trump as their 'ray of hope' |last=McKenzie |first=David |last2=Swails |first2=Brent |date=November 2019 |website=www.cnn.com |publisher=CNN |access-date=6 April 2019}}</ref> a spokesperson for the racist, [[ethnonationalist]] ([[v\u00f6lkisch]]) Afrikaner organization [[Suidlanders]].<ref name=\"ARD - AfD Suidlander\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.tagesschau.de/inland/bystron-103.html |title=AfD-Politiker in S\u00fcdafrika: Schie\u00dftraining mit Rassisten |last=Staff |date=18 December 2018 |work=tagesschau.de |access-date=5 April 2019 |publisher=[[ARD (broadcaster)|ARD]] |language=de |trans-title=AfD Politician in South Africa: Shooting Practice With Racists |quote=Nach Einsch\u00e4tzung von Gareth Newham vom s\u00fcdafrikanischen Institute for Security Studies in Pretoria handelt es sich bei den \"Suidlanders\" um einen Zusammenschluss von v\u00f6lkischen Rassisten: \"Ihre Ideologie ist die \u00dcberlegenheit der wei\u00dfen Rasse\", sagte Newham. \"Ihr einziger Existenzgrund ist die angebliche Verteidigung gegen die Schwarzen. Man kann sie eindeutig als rassistische v\u00f6lkische Organisation beschreiben. [According to Gareth Newham of the South African Institute for Security Studies in Pretoria, the \"Suidlanders\" constitute an association of populist Racists: \"Their ideology is the survival of the white race,\" says Newham. \"Their singular reason for existing is to supposedly defend against blacks. One can clearly describe them as a racist populist organization\"]}}</ref><ref name=\"vice_suidelanders\">{{cite news |last1=Haynes |first1=Gavin |title=The Race War Preppers Behind South Africa's 'White Genocide' Meme |url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/qvn44v/the-race-war-preppers-behind-south-africas-white-genocide-meme |accessdate=6 April 2019 |work=Vice News |date=10 May 2019}}</ref> In 2017, Southern produced a video on [[the Great Replacement conspiracy theory]], which posits that non-white immigration will lead to a \"genocide\" of white Europeans.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Weitzmann |first1=Marc |title=The Global Language of Hatred Is French |journal=Foreign Affairs |date=1 April 2019 |url=https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/new-zealand/2019-04-01/global-language-hatred-french |accessdate=2 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Tharoor |first1=Ishaan |title=The racist theory that underlies terrorism in New Zealand and the Trump presidency |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2019/03/18/racist-theory-that-links-terror-new-zealand-trump-presidency |accessdate=2 April 2019 |work=The Washington Post |date=18 March 2019}}</ref> Southern's Documentary on [[South African farm attacks|South Africa farm attacks]]  is credited with helping to popularize the conspiracy theory.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Miller |first1=Nick |title='The Great Replacement': an idea now at the heart of Europe's politics |url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/europe/the-great-replacement-the-racist-idea-now-at-the-heart-of-europe-s-politics-20190319-p515cc.html |accessdate=4 April 2019 |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=19 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Religion===\nWhen she was asked about her religion, specifically to the question whether she is [[Christianity|Christian]], she stated she is not, but that she is \"searching\".<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3MYjY9yddy0&t=5m46s Lauren Southern Fights Back Against Establishment Media], ''Rebel Media'', 20 Jan 2017, Accessed 13 Feb 2017</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{commons}}\n*{{official website}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Southern, Lauren}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Alt-right writers]]\n[[Category:Canadian anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Canadian documentary film producers]]\n[[Category:Canadian libertarians]]\n[[Category:Canadian media personalities]]\n[[Category:Canadian political writers]]\n[[Category:Canadian social commentators]]\n[[Category:Canadian women in federal politics]]\n[[Category:Canadian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Critics of multiculturalism]]\n[[Category:Critics of Islam]]\n[[Category:Far-right politics in Canada]]\n[[Category:Female critics of feminism]]\n[[Category:Libertarianism in Canada]]\n[[Category:Libertarian Party of Canada candidates for the Canadian House of Commons]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Opposition to Islam in Canada]]\n[[Category:People from Surrey, British Columbia]]\n[[Category:The Great Replacement conspiracy theorists]]\n[[Category:Writers from British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Women documentary filmmakers]]\n", "name_user": "Aitch & Aitch Aitch", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lauren_Southern"}
